#Summary1=(human1) The team of Project London, a sci-fi film with tie-in products, talk about the experience of making the film, the tie-in graphic novel, the creative process, marketing the film at conventions, and the next steps for the team.

#Summary2=(claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022) Project London has two tie-in products (a graphic novel and novella) created by Branson Anderson and Caleb Wheeler, and the team plans to promote the film through conventions while working on other projects like Geekseekers, Gamers 3, and freelance work in 2013.

#Summary3=(gpt4o) Benjamin Gerber and Phil McCoy discuss Project London, highlighting the tie-in graphic novel and novella, detailing creative contributions from Branson Anderson and Caleb Wheeler, marketing strategies, and future plans for the project, as well as mentioning upcoming conventions and personal projects from team members like Jen Page and Ian Hubert for 2013.

#Summary4=(Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct) The podcast discusses the graphic novel and novella tie-ins for the movie Project London, featuring artists Branson Anderson and Caleb Wheeler, and discusses marketing plans for the film.

#Summary5=(Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct) The creator of Project London discusses the release of the graphic novel and novella tie-ins to the film, upcoming conventions, and future projects including Geekseekers, ChopSockyBoom, and personal short films.
#Text=And speaking of comic books and graphic novels and novellas , uh , there 's a couple of tie - in products for Project London as well .
#Text=There is the graphic novel and a novella that were released was this last year ?
#Text=Am I correct in saying that ?
#Text=Well , I think it 's just about a year and a half , almost two years .
#Text=Um , and we 're really proud of those items and people who are associated with the project , uh , Caleb Wheeler , Branson Anderson .

#Text=Uh um uh uh , gosh , you know , I remember Branson , uh , on set , has his sketchbook with him , and he 's noodling around ideas of what 's happening that day and making characters in this , this , uh , idea gel .
#Text=And , uh , probably a year later , after we were in post-production , I asked Branson , you know , would you be interested in doing a graphic novel , and he jumped on it , and here we are .

#Text=Uh , Caleb , is a film student and , uh , writer , and , uh , his dad 's a friend of mine , uh , and his dad was talking to me one day , and he -- I think he 's got -- he told me he 's got like , 60 or 70 manuscripts on the shelf .
#Text=And I thought , uh , whoa , you know kids !
#Text=And I , his dad , you know , we 're on a wavelength .
#Text=And I could ask him , can he tell a story ?
#Text=Right .
#Text=And he could .
#Text=And I connected him with Ian , and we did a few chapters as a test , and it passed muster .
#Text=And we now have the story of how the Malardians showed up on planet Earth , during World War II , and Project London .
#Text=Excellent .

#Text=And you sent me the PDF , I believe , of the graphic novel and the novella as well , back when it came out a year and a half ago , and I think I have a review on my site , so I 'll -- I 'll link back -- that back to that as well .
#Text=Uh , if folks wanted to get a hold of those , how would they go about doing that ?

#Text=The best way to get a hold of the Project Manhattan or the graphic novel is to just visit , uh , the official movie website , projectlondonmovie.com , click on the books link , and you can preview them there , and you can find all of the links to purchase .
#Text=Excellent .
#Text=And Branson not only created the graphic novel , but I mean , he acted in the film as well .
#Text=We should -- we should mention that too .
#Text=So you 've got actors , you 've got artists , you 've got graphic novelists , you 've got computer specialists .
#Text=Which one of you sings ?
#Text=No .
#Text=No .
#Text=So we ca 'nt Project London Chorus at the end of this podcast .
#Text=That 's not going to be happening , right ?
#Text=Yeah , if we have had West over here for this interview --
#Text=West was our soundtrack producer and , uh , uh , did some amazing work .
#Text=And when you get a chance to see the movie , Ben , um , it 'll rip your face off .
#Text=I heard -- I 've heard it will rip my face off , and I am chomping at the bit to see this .
#Text=I can not wait for this movie to come out .

#Text=I mean , first there was this , and then The Hobbit kind of bumped in , but The Hobbit is going to be over soon , and then I 'm going back to Project London and I 'm serious , I really can not wait to see this film .
#Text=I 've been following it for so long and to actually see this thing , it 's just going to be amazing , ca n't wait .
#Text=Um , so once you 're done with a Kickstarter and everything is set , you 're -- you 're going to shop it around to a couple festivals , you said .
#Text=How else are you going to spread the word ?
#Text=I mean , you have a pretty decent present presence online , but what else are you guys going to do ?
#Text=Do you have any other plans ?
#Text=Yeah , we do have conventions .
#Text=We 've got 6 to 8 conventions lined up already .
#Text=Wow .
#Text=Um , including , uh , GenCon , Indiana .
#Text=And , um , that event , I think , could be as big as we can make it , but , um , it does n't take much , really , to contact conventions and ship out a screener to them .
#Text=It 's not like we have to pay for airfare for everyone to go out and just start grassroots spreading the word .
#Text=Um , I do n't know .
#Text=Personally , I 'm just so hungry for good sci - fi .
#Text=Yeah .
#Text=I know people are just going to eat this up .
#Text=Now , if I happen to be a guest at a convention in February , is that too early to set something up ?
#Text=I hope not .
#Text=Yeah , I hope not .
#Text=If you 've got some ideas , we 'd love to hear them .
#Text=I 'll have to get back in touch .
#Text=Sorry , but I did n't mean to step on it .
#Text=Um , this this whole thing has been a journey of discovery all along the way .
#Text=And we talk about , you know , marketing plans and how can we make more noise .
#Text=You know , we 're figuring it out every day .
#Text=What can we do ?
#Text=And then we do it .
#Text=And that 's the way it 's been .
#Text=Well , excellent .
#Text=Um , I do happen to have a convention I 'll be going to in February , uh , so I love to set that up .
#Text=And I 'm also going to be --
#Text=I do n't know if you guys have , uh , thought about Pax East at all , um , but , uh , that that that 's also a possibility .
#Text=Yeah , yeah .
#Text=You know , I 've been so myopic around the idea that it 's Kickstarter packaged and done .
#Text=In fact , once it was launched , that 's all that 's had my attention .
#Text=Mhm , um , but as soon as we get a little further along with that , we 'll , uh , we 'll start looking at , you know , 2013 and booking then .
#Text=Excellent .
#Text=Very cool .
#Text=And then Project London 2 .
#Text=Now what personally -- what do you guys have coming down the pipeline ?
#Text=Because I -- I imagine as this thing is wrapping up , you 're either going to take a really long vacation or you 're going to think about your next project .
#Text=So what do you guys have coming up ?
#Text=Oh , geez .
#Text=Well , I 'm certainly focused on Geekseekers right now .
#Text=Yeah .

#Text=And um , premiering that , we want to line up a few episodes so that they can go out the door instead of releasing one and going , oh , uh , and , uh , Chop Socky Boom as well , uh , just wrapped on Gamers 3 .
#Text=Mhm .
#Text=Um , that 's that 's another big exciting thing .
#Text=And I also have a few projects of my own that I 'm developing .
#Text=I 've got two short films in the future that I would love to see happen someday .
#Text=I 'm just -- I 've been mostly doing freelance and stuff .
#Text=Um , kind of trying to work on , on smaller stuff just kind of for the contrast .
#Text=Sure .
#Text=Um , but , uh , because every project is kind of throwing it at the wall , seeing what sticks , um , kind of a learning experience .
#Text=Um , I 've learned so much from Project London , but , um , it 's fun to try to implement that now , like , just kind of short stuff .
#Text=You know , 2013 is going to be the year of Project London .
#Text=And that 's that 's where my energy is going to be .
#Text=And while that 's happening , I 'm -- I 'm going to be looking out for the next thing .
#Text=I do n't know what I want to be when I grow up .
#Text=And just might find it in 2013 .
#Text=I think that yeah , yeah .
#Text=I have a feature .
#Text=Yeah , yeah , I was just going to say Jen has a feature .
